text.section:
If a person made a security deposit of money under the financial responsibility law as it existed before January 1, 1973, the person or his personal representative may apply to the Maryland Automobile Insurance Fund for and is entitled to a refund of the deposit, without interest, if:
An action for damages arising out of the accident for which the deposit was made is not pending against the person on whose behalf the deposit was made;
An unpaid judgment does not exist in favor of any person as a result of an action arising from the accident for which the deposit was made;
A claim is not pending against the Unsatisfied Claim and Judgment Fund Board or its successor for damages arising out of the accident for which the deposit was made; and
The executive director of the Maryland Automobile Insurance Fund, on the advice of the Attorney General, is satisfied by a reasonable preponderance of the evidence that the person is legally entitled to the deposit.
